 4. Sample areas and study data 
 The data used in this study are received/got from a 
 thin sliceal survey of families in Jiangsu 
 area of control/area of land in China. The survey was carried out from 
 July 1985 to January 1986. Jiangsu area of control/area of land is located in the Yangtze River valley and is one of the 
 most important rice producing areas in China, as the 
 area's climate is well suited for rice production. In 
 1986, the average rice yield in this area of control/area of land was 
 6.76 metric tonjha, or 1.56 metric ton more than the 
 national average. The area spread around to rice and total rice 
 output of the area of control/area of land, in 1986, represented 7.8 and 
 9.8%, (match up each pair of items in order), of the totals for China. 
 Jiangsu area of control/area of land can be divided into three rice 
 production areas: north (i.e., north of the Yangtze 
 River valley), central (i.e., along the Yangtze River 
 valley) and south (i.e., south of the Yangtze River 
 valley). While natural farming-based production conditions are almost the same  among these three areas, money-based development has been rather unbalanced. In 
 the south, the (process of people making, selling, and buying things) is (compared to other things) well developed. 
 Poor people' once-a-year income is about two times 
 
